This saves us some space since we‚Äôre dropping a column, but isn‚Äôt the prettiest thing. Let‚Äôs use an anonymous function and text_transform to change the styling of our player‚Äôs name/team with <span style> along with small caps, different font colors and sizes.


ex_tab %>%
  cols_merge(
    columns = vars(last_name, team)
  ) %>% 
  text_transform(
    locations = cells_body(
      columns = vars(last_name)
    ),
    fn = function(x){
      name <- word(x, 1)
      team <- word(x, -1)
      glue::glue(
        "<div><span style='font-weight:bold;font-variant:small-caps;font-size:14px'>{name}</div>
        <div><span style ='font-weight:bold;color:grey;font-size:10px'>{team}</span></div>"
      )
    }
  )


