This tells us something interesting! It‚Äôs combined all the vectors into a character string separated by commas. No wonder our graph can‚Äôt understand its xy coords, it is passed as one long text string!
Now if we‚Äôre tricky, we can get at the guts of gt since it‚Äôs just a list object. There‚Äôs quite a bit there inside the gt object, but the first list item is arguably the most important! We have the raw data as _data!


mtcars %>% 
  group_by(cyl) %>% 
  summarize(mpg_data = list(mpg), .groups = "drop") %>% 
  gt() %>% 
  str(max.level = 1)


