We can pluck() the raw underlying data itself from gt, extract the mpg_data column, and could work with it in our function.


mtcars %>% 
  group_by(cyl) %>% 
  summarize(mpg_data = list(as.double(mpg)), .groups = "drop") %>% 
  gt() %>% 
  pluck("_data", "mpg_data") %>% 
  str()


