gt tables
I‚Äôm continuing my series on gt tables with an exploration of gt functions and themes. Technically, they could be treated as the same thing but slightly different use cases.
For a function - I would think of the gt table as the final output, whereas a theme is applied to an existing gt table.


library(tidyverse)
library(gt)
library(espnscrapeR)



If you‚Äôve never written a function, I‚Äôd recommend reading the functions chapter from the R4DS book.
For an example, here‚Äôs a quick function with gt:


mtcars_table <- function(cyl_match = 6){
  mtcars %>% 
    filter(cyl == cyl_match) %>% 
    head() %>% 
    gt() %>% 
    tab_header(
      title = glue::glue("Table for cars with {cyl_match} cylinders")
    )
}

mtcars_table(4)


