Been following Dave Robinson‚Äôs Tidy Simulation Series in #rstatsand decided to try and give it a go.
We play a dice game called ‚Äú10,000‚Äù in my wife‚Äôs family. The family of games also includes Ten Grand, Farkle, Zilch, and others according to Wikipedia - with the common thread being that you have 5-6 dice, roll them, and add up scoring dice until you stop with a set score or ‚Äúzippy‚Äù, which is a roll with zero scoring die.
Basic gist: - Roll 5 dice - If you ‚Äúscore‚Äù with at least one die, you can stay or keep rolling - If you roll zero scoring die, you lose your turn
