 4            1     4
 5            1     5
 6            2     1
 7            2     2
 8            2     3
 9            2     4
10            2     5
# ‚Ä¶ with 15 more rows

For, the actual dataframe we‚Äôll do an additional step, which is creating a vector of rolls with random sampling based on how many dice are in hand. For our 1:5 dice in hand + 10,000 samples per dice in hand we get 50,000 simulations.


set.seed(37)
n_rolls <- 10000

# Generate a sample of rolls (10000 sims)
dice_rolls <- crossing(dice_in_hand = seq(1, 5, 1),
                       trial = 1:n_rolls) %>%
  mutate(roll = map(dice_in_hand, ~ sample(1:6, ., replace = TRUE)))

dice_rolls


